    "[15], this mechanism is indeed realized here.",
    "Denoting ϑ = arg( m), where m is defined in Eq.",
    "( 3), two of the vacua of the Z + q order, namely ϑ = 0 and ϑ = π, are invariant under the residual symmetry T: ϑ → -ϑ.",
    "As a result, inside the Z + q AFM ⊕ Z 2 NM phase, any smooth domain wall between the ϑ = 0 and ϑ = π regions traps a T charge (see Fig. 6), and the Z + q order parameter cos(qϑ/2) that is finite elsewhere vanishes at the domain wall.",
    "The Z - q order parameter sin(qϑ/2) has the opposite behavior and becomes finite only at the domain wall."
